From fd20124cc2a9d27b158f0891f86e931740185b6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tcfialho <tcfialho@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 23:55:03 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] maindeck anim Step 1: position tween + open fade

Tween engine (river/Animation.zig) interpolates window position and opacity
locally in the output frame loop, instead of snapping to the geometry targets
the wm sends. Animation state lives inline on Window (anim: ?Animation), null
in steady state for zero idle cost.

- renderFinish arms a move tween (re-targets from last-applied position if one
  is in flight) or an open fade on first show; snaps when fullscreen/first map.
- handleFrame advances all tweens before renderAndCommit so node mutations
  damage the same frame, and reschedules only while something is animating.
- opacity is applied per SceneBuffer via forEachBuffer (no tree-level opacity).

Position + open fade only; close fade and size/spring (texture-scale) are next.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
